benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/catalog/phase - Retrieve phase for a given subscription and date

covered: Valid Request: TC01 exercises retrieval with both subscriptionId and requestedDate; TC02 covers retrieval with only subscriptionId; TC03/TC04 cover invalid/missing parameter combinations and error handling; TC05/TC06/TC07/TC08 cover non-existent data and invalid formats; TC09 covers unauthorized access; TC10 covers system/dependency failure; TC11 tests security (SQL injection); TC12 handles empty database edge case; TC13 covers large datasets performance considerations; TC14 verifies extra parameters are ignored; TC15 checks boundary date behavior; TC16 covers concurrent requests and performance expectations; Authorization scenarios are addressed (401); Error handling scenarios (400/404/422/500 family) are represented across multiple tests.
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for pagination behavior when large datasets are involved (even though TC13 mentions large datasets, there is no assertion of paginated responses).
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache validity are present.
Rate Limiting: No tests assessing how the API handles burst or repeated rapid requests.
Fine-grained authorization beyond 401 (e.g., 403) or scope-based access control is not explicitly tested.
Default/ambiguous return when only subscriptionId is provided (TC02) could be expanded with explicit expectations for default phase or null behavior for edge cases.
Boundary and edge-case date handling around exact phase-change moments could be expanded with more diverse boundary scenarios.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests for /1.0/kb/catalog/phase when the dataset contains many subscriptions/phases to verify correct page sizing, offsets, and total counts.
Add tests to validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and behavior on successive identical requests.
Introduce rate-limiting tests to ensure proper throttling or error responses under burst traffic.
Extend authorization tests to cover additional scopes/roles and 403 Forbidden responses, not just 401 Unauthorized.
Clarify and add explicit expectations for TC02 (only subscriptionId) in edge scenarios, including default phase behavior and null responses when data is sparse.
Enhance boundary-date test coverage with multiple boundary dates across several phase transitions to ensure correct phase resolution near changes.
